---
import { getEmDashEntry } from "emdash";
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import PageHero from "../components/PageHero.astro";
import LocationSection from "../components/LocationSection.astro";
import ServicesSection from "../components/ServicesSection.astro";

const memberEntry = await getEmDashEntry("team", "dr-tiffany-brewer").catch(() => null);
const member = memberEntry?.data ?? {};
const photoSrc = member.photo?.src ?? "/uploads/7854b158e5b131e9a356dfaafa022012ce061557.jpg";
---

<Base
	title="Dr. Tiffany Brewer, Au.D."
	description="Tiffany Brewer is an audiologist providing hearing tests, hearing aids, and other hearing care services in Georgetown, KY."
>
	<PageHero
		title="Dr. Tiffany Brewer, Au.D."
		breadcrumbs={[
			{ label: "Home", href: "/" },
			{ label: "About", href: "/about/" },
			{ label: "Dr. Tiffany Brewer" },
		]}
		image="/uploads/tiffany-brewer-hero.jpg"
		meta="Doctor of Audiology"
	/>

	<section class="bio-section">
		<div class="bio-grid">
			<div class="bio-main">
				<p class="bio-lead" {...memberEntry?.edit?.bio}>
					{member.bio ?? "Tiffany Brewer is an audiologist providing hearing tests, hearing aids, and other hearing care services in Georgetown, KY."}
				</p>
				<p>
					At the heart of Commonwealth Audiology is Dr. Tiffany Brewer, a
					knowledgeable, compassionate, and deeply committed audiologist who
					believes that hearing well is essential to living well. Her
					approach blends clinical excellence with genuine care, ensuring
					every patient feels heard, supported, and confidently guided on
					their hearing journey. She is passionate about helping people
					reconnect, not just to sound, but to relationships and moments
					that matter most.
				</p>

				<h2>Education &amp; Professional Expertise</h2>
				<p>
					Dr. Tiffany Brewer earned her Doctor of Audiology (Au.D.) from the
					University of Louisville School of Medicine, where she developed a
					strong foundation in diagnostic testing, hearing science, and
					patient-centered care. She completed her undergraduate studies at
					Miami University in Oxford, Ohio, earning a degree in Speech
					Pathology and Audiology with a minor in Special Education, an
					experience that deepened her passion for communication and helping
					others thrive.
				</p>
				<p>
					She is licensed by the state of Kentucky as an Audiologist and
					remains actively involved in several respected professional
					organizations, including:
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Academy of Doctors of Audiology (ADA) - Member</li>
					<li>American Academy of Audiology (AAA) - Professional Member</li>
					<li>Audiology Practice Standards Organization (ASPO) - Member</li>
					<li>Entheos Audiology Cooperative - Member</li>
					<li>HearingUp Provider</li>
					<li>Kentucky Academy of Audiology (KAA) - Member and Current President</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					In addition to her clinical work, Dr. Brewer is a strong advocate
					for the audiology profession and the patients it serves. She has
					lobbied in Washington, DC for improved access to audiology care and
					continues to champion the full scope of audiology practice. She has
					also worked closely with the Kentucky Audiology Board to help
					modernize current licensure standards, supporting the advancement
					and accessibility of high-quality hearing healthcare. Her active
					involvement, particularly her leadership role as President of the
					Kentucky Academy of Audiology, reflects her commitment to advancing
					the field and staying at the forefront of best practices in hearing
					healthcare.
				</p>

				<h2>Her Clinical Focus</h2>
				<p>Dr. Brewer specializes in:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Comprehensive diagnostic audiologic evaluations</li>
					<li>Hearing aid selection and fitting</li>
					<li>Real-ear measurements and precision programming</li>
					<li>Long-term follow-up care and counseling</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					She takes a highly personalized approach to care, recognizing that
					no two patients, and no two hearing losses, are exactly the same. By
					combining advanced diagnostic tools with careful listening and
					attention to detail, she creates tailored solutions that support
					each patient's unique lifestyle and communication goals.
				</p>
				<p>
					Dr. Brewer places a strong emphasis on precision and verification,
					using best-practice methods like real-ear measurements to ensure
					hearing aids are programmed accurately from the start. This level of
					detail helps reduce frustration and leads to better long-term
					outcomes.
				</p>

				<h2>A Thoughtful, Patient-First Approach</h2>
				<p>
					Patients often remark on how comfortable and supported they feel
					under Dr. Brewer's care. She takes the time to explain results
					clearly, answer questions thoroughly, and guide each person through
					their options without pressure. Her focus goes beyond improving
					hearing, she strives to help patients feel confident, clear, and at
					ease in their everyday lives.
				</p>
				<p>
					For individuals experiencing hearing loss, she strongly believes in
					early evaluation and personalized treatment. Her message is simple:
					there are always options, and she is there to help each patient find
					the right path forward.
				</p>

				<h2>A Passion for Helping People Reconnect</h2>
				<p>
					What truly sets Dr. Brewer apart is her heart for people. She loves
					seeing her patients regain confidence, reconnect with loved ones,
					and rediscover the sounds that make life meaningful. She considers
					it an honor to walk alongside each person as they regain or improve
					their hearing.
				</p>

				<h2>Life Outside the Clinic</h2>
				<p>
					When she's not caring for patients, Dr. Brewer enjoys spending time
					with her husband, daughters, son, and their family pup. Her family
					is active in Crossroads Christian Church, and she loves being part
					of the Georgetown community. In her free time, you'll often find her
					exploring the beauty of the Bluegrass region, spending time on the
					water, or baking for family and friends.
				</p>

				<h2>A Doctor Who Treats You Like Family</h2>
				<p>
					At Commonwealth Audiology, Dr. Brewer has created a practice where
					patients feel welcomed, understood, and genuinely cared for. With
					advanced training, a commitment to excellence, and a heartfelt
					approach, she provides expert, individualized care you can trust.
				</p>
				<p>
					If you or someone you love is experiencing hearing difficulties, Dr.
					Brewer is here to help you take the next step toward clearer hearing
					and a more connected life.
				</p>
			</div>

			<aside class="bio-aside">
				<div class="bio-photo-card">
					<img src={photoSrc} alt="Dr. Tiffany Brewer, Au.D." class="bio-photo" {...memberEntry?.edit?.photo} />
					<div class="bio-photo-meta">
						<p class="bio-photo-name" {...memberEntry?.edit?.name}>{member.name ?? "Dr. Tiffany Brewer, Au.D."}</p>
						<p class="bio-photo-role" {...memberEntry?.edit?.role}>{member.role ?? "Doctor of Audiology"}</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</aside>
		</div>

	</section>

	<LocationSection />
	<ServicesSection />
</Base>

<style>
	.bio-section {
		background: #fff;
		padding: 3.5rem 1.5rem 1rem;
	}

	.bio-grid {
		max-width: 1200px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) 360px;
		gap: 3rem;
		align-items: start;
	}

	.bio-main {
		min-width: 0;
		color: #1a1a1a;
	}

	.bio-main p {
		margin: 0 0 1.15rem;
		font-size: 1.075rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: #1a1a1a;
	}

	.bio-eyebrow {
		font-size: 0.95rem !important;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: #0076ba;
		margin-bottom: 0.4rem !important;
	}

	.bio-lead {
		font-style: italic;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.bio-main h2 {
		margin: 2.3rem 0 1rem;
		font-family: "Merriweather", Georgia, serif;
		font-size: 1.95rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1.2;
		color: #1f1f1f;
	}

	.bio-main ul {
		margin: 0 0 1.2rem;
		padding-left: 1.5rem;
	}

	.bio-main li {
		margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
		font-size: 1.075rem;
		line-height: 1.55;
		color: #1a1a1a;
	}

	/* ── Photo (right column) ── */
	.bio-aside {
		position: sticky;
		top: 120px;
	}

	.bio-photo-card {
		border-radius: 16px;
		overflow: hidden;
		background: #fff;
		box-shadow: 0 12px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.14);
	}

	.bio-photo {
		display: block;
		width: 100%;
		height: auto;
		aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
		object-fit: cover;
	}

	.bio-photo-meta {
		padding: 1.2rem 1.4rem 1.4rem;
		text-align: center;
		background: #0076ba;
	}

	.bio-photo-name {
		margin: 0 0 0.2rem;
		font-family: "Merriweather", Georgia, serif;
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
	}

	.bio-photo-role {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
	}

	/* ── Staff bios (full width) ── */
	.bio-staff {
		max-width: 1200px;
		margin: 2.5rem auto 0;
		color: #1a1a1a;
	}

	.bio-staff h2 {
		margin: 0 0 1rem;
		font-family: "Merriweather", Georgia, serif;
		font-size: 1.95rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #1f1f1f;
	}

	.bio-staff h3 {
		margin: 1.8rem 0 0.7rem;
		font-family: "Merriweather", Georgia, serif;
		font-size: 1.4rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #1f1f1f;
	}

	.bio-staff p {
		margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
		font-size: 1.075rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	@media (max-width: 960px) {
		.bio-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: 2rem;
		}
		.bio-aside {
			position: static;
			order: -1;
			max-width: 360px;
		}
		.bio-main h2,
		.bio-staff h2 {
			font-size: 1.7rem;
		}
	}
</style>
